4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LICENSE FEES FOR MIGRATORY GAME BIRDS;
5 CREATING FEES FOR SANDHILL CRANE AND SWAN APPLICATIONS AND LICENSES; REVISING THE
6 MIGRATORY GAME BIRD LICENSE FEE; PROVIDING FOR FUNDS FROM SANDHILL CRANE AND SWAN
7 LICENSE SALES TO BE DEPOSITED IN THE DEPARTMENT SPECIAL REVENUE ACCOUNT; AMENDING
8 SECTIONS 87-2-113 AND 87-2-411, MCA; AND PROVIDING A DELAYED EFFECTIVE DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 Section 1. Section 87-2-113, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "87-2-113. Application fees. (1) (a) Except as provided in subsection (1)(b), when the department
14 determines a drawing is necessary prior to issuance of hunting licenses for any game species during a hunting
15 season, it shall collect a $5 per species application fee.
16 (b) The department shall collect the following per species special license application fees:
17 (i) moose--resident, $10; nonresident, $50;
18 (ii) mountain goat--resident, $10; nonresident, $50;
19 (iii) mountain sheep--resident, $10; nonresident, $50;
20 (iv) sandhill crane--resident, $10; nonresident, $50;
21 (v) swan--resident, $10; nonresident, $50;
22 (iv)(vi) wild buffalo or bison--resident, $10; nonresident, $50.
23 (2) (a) If a resident participates in the bonus point system adopted by the commission, the
24 department shall collect an additional application fee of $2 per species.
25 (b) If a nonresident participates in the bonus point system adopted by the commission, the
26 department shall collect an additional application fee of $20 per species.
27 (3) Application fees collected pursuant to this section must be deposited in the state special
28 revenue fund to the credit of the department as set forth in 87-1-601.
